Royal Canin WhatsApp Care Concierge &  Quick-Commerce

The Core Concept
Prescription pet food (veterinary diets) often has a high friction-to-purchase funnel:
A veterinarian diagnoses the pet and recommends a specific diet formulation.
The owner has to search multiple local pet stores or wait several days for specialized e-commerce delivery.
This friction causes significant drop-offs, leaving pets without their necessary therapeutic nutrition.
Our Solution:

A seamless, single-screen experience that emulates a real WhatsApp Business account. The user onboarding feeds diagnostic data (pet age, breed, weight, medical conditions) into a Recommendation Engine. When a recommendation is formulated, Zepto Quick Commerce is synced directly inside the WhatsApp bubble, executing a live 3-step warehouse check and ending with a Complete UPI Checkout directly in-chat.
🚀 Key Features
💬 Authentic WhatsApp Simulation: Fully immersive, responsive mobile viewport simulating a live WhatsApp Chat session.
📋 Dynamic Pet Onboarding & Diagnostic Engine: Captures key health indicators (e.g., skin allergies, digestive sensitivities, weight management) to pinpoint the exact Royal Canin Veterinary Diet required.
🛒 In-Chat Multi-Product Formulation Shelf: When the user requests to "order" or "buy", a dynamic carousel displays a curated list of relevant Royal Canin products matching their pet's size and medical needs (rather than just a single option), complete with dynamic weight/size selectors and pricing.
⚡ In-Chat Quick-Commerce Sync: An interactive, live 3-step stepper that simulates background automation:
Verifying pet profile / parsing clinic formulation.
Locking down local Zepto warehouse stock.
Routing rapid delivery paths (10-minute dispatch).
💳 Unified UPI Checkout: A fully integrated, real-time simulated UPI Payment modal directly within the WhatsApp feed, preventing users from ever having to leave the app to purchase.
📈 Value & Strategic Benefits for Royal Canin (RC)

Unprecedented Conversion Rates: By collapsing the time-to-purchase from days/hours to seconds, conversion rates are optimized. Users buy their prescription food instantly after their vet or chatbot recommendation.
First-Party Health Data Collection: RC gains structured data regarding pet demographics, breed distributions, and localized health concerns to optimize product inventory and target localized marketing campaigns.
Elevated Brand Trust: By pairing high-quality clinical food with top-tier veterinary advice and rapid delivery, Royal Canin cements its role as a premium, pet-first health organization.
Combating Channel Leakage: Prevents consumers from switching to generic or non-prescription alternatives during the gap between leaving the clinic and purchasing food.
🔮 Future Scope & Production Roadmap
